@Node Updates "Information about updates"

                         @{b}Where can you get updates?@{ub}
                         --------------------------

The "IDEfix-CD32-Emulator-Support-Guide" will always be available
at the following @{b}BBSes@{ub}:

o  @{" Spy Box " link SpyBox}
   -> ++49-(0)-3869-58012 (both: analogous/ISDN, V.34/X.75, 28.800/64.000 BPS)
   -> ++49-(0)-3869-58013 (both: analogous/ISDN, V.34/X.75, 28.800/64.000)

   See the board "Bin/Amiga/Disk"

o  @{" Vesalia BBS " link Vesalia}
   -> ++49-(0)-2852-914016 (analogous, V.34+, 33.600 BPS)
   -> ++49-(0)-2852-914017 (analogous, V.34 , 28.800)
   -> ++49-(0)-2852-914018 (ISDN     , X.75 , 64.000)

   See the board "Binaer/Amiga/Disk/CDROM"

You can also find it in @{b}Aminet@{ub} in the "disk/cdrom"-area! The name
of the archive will always be "IDEfixCD32Guid.lha".

Another possibility is to @{b}send me your request@{ub}. I'll send you the
archive via e-mail. Just do the following steps:
o  Send your mail to <Tommy@SpyBox.shnet.org>
o  Subject: "Send IDEfixCD32Guide.lha"
o  Mail body: Just tell me if you want the archive to be sent uuendoded
              (The way you write this isn't important).

I think it is not necessary to say that it's worth visiting the @{b}homepage@{ub}
@{b}of "Elaborate Bytes"@{ub}, just try "http://www.elaborate-bytes.com"! :-)
@Endnode

